# Customization Code Template
# Use this template when adding new custom modifications to browserless

# For complete code blocks (recommended for major modifications):

// ========== [CUSTOMIZED START] ==========
// Purpose: [Brief description of what this modification does]
// Date: [YYYY-MM-DD]
// Modified by: [Your name or team name]
// Related: [Related feature, issue number, or PR reference]
// ========== [CUSTOMIZED] ==========

[Your custom code goes here]

// ========== [CUSTOMIZED END] ==========


# For inline comments (recommended for simple one-line changes):

someCode(); // [CUSTOMIZED] Brief explanation of the modification


# Guidelines:

1. Always add [CUSTOMIZED] markers to make code searchable
2. Include a clear purpose/explanation
3. Date the modification for tracking
4. Update CUSTOMIZATIONS.md with details of the change
5. Use complete blocks for multi-line modifications
6. Use inline comments for single-line changes
7. Keep explanations concise but informative

# Examples:

## Example 1: Adding a new configuration property

// ========== [CUSTOMIZED START] ==========
// Purpose: Add support for custom browser timeout configuration
// Date: 2025-11-01
// Modified by: Vincent
// Related: Custom timeout feature
// ========== [CUSTOMIZED] ==========
protected customBrowserTimeout = process.env.CUSTOM_BROWSER_TIMEOUT
  ? parseInt(process.env.CUSTOM_BROWSER_TIMEOUT, 10)
  : 30000;

public getCustomBrowserTimeout(): number {
  return this.customBrowserTimeout;
}
// ========== [CUSTOMIZED END] ==========


## Example 2: Modifying an existing function call

const result = await someFunction(this.config); // [CUSTOMIZED] Pass config parameter for custom path support


## Example 3: Adding conditional logic

// ========== [CUSTOMIZED START] ==========
// Purpose: Skip validation for custom browser configurations
// Date: 2025-11-01
// ========== [CUSTOMIZED] ==========
if (config.getCustomChromiumPath()) {
  this.logger.info('Using custom browser configuration, skipping validation');
  return true;
}
// ========== [CUSTOMIZED END] ==========


# Search commands:

# Find all customizations:
grep -rn "CUSTOMIZED" src/ .env.dev

# Find complete blocks only:
grep -A 3 "CUSTOMIZED START" src/

# Count total customizations:
grep -r "CUSTOMIZED" src/ .env.dev | wc -l


# Remember:
- Keep customizations minimal and well-documented
- Always update CUSTOMIZATIONS.md when adding new modifications
- Test thoroughly after making changes
- Consider upstream compatibility when modifying core functionality
